⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Old Major
node AFM · AFM · ⟦Old Major:AFM:0b9c34⟧

WHO   — Old Major — the dream of revolution
WHAT  — The originating ideal: he teaches Animalism and the song ‘Beasts of England,’ then dies before the revolt he inspired.
WHERE — AFM · ANIMAL FARM  Framework inputs: Animal Farm (George Orwell, 1945)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because every revolution needs its prophet — and the purity of the dream is measured against what's made of it.
HOW   — By a barn-speech vision of equality and the anthem that carries it, planted before he can see it betrayed.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I dreamed a farm without masters and sang it to them once — and died before I could see the pigs put on the master's coat.

